            h2 1. Keep Your HTML Structure Clean and Organized
            p A clean and well-organized HTML structure helps search engines crawl your site more efficiently. Use proper nesting and indentation.
            h3 Example
            pre
              code
                | <header>
                |   <h1>Welcome</h1>
                |   <p>Some content here</p>
                | </header>

            section
              h2 2. Use Semantic HTML Tags
              p Semantic tags like header, main, section, and article define the purpose of your content, improving accessibility and helping search engines understand your site better.

            section
              h2 3. Optimize Links and Images
              ul
                li
                  strong Clear Links:
                  | Use descriptive anchor text like:
                  pre
                    code
                      | <a href="contact.html">Contact Us</a>
                  | Instead of generic text like "Click Here."
                li
                  strong Alt Tags for Images:
                  | Always describe your images:
                  pre
                    code
                      | <img src="seo-tips.jpg" alt="SEO Tips for Beginners">

            section
              h2 4. Leverage Meta Tags
              p Meta tags provide essential information to search engines about your page. Each page should have a unique Meta Title and Meta Description.
              h3 Example
              pre
                code
                  | <meta name="title" content="Learn HTML for Better SEO">
                  | <meta name="description" content="Discover how HTML structure impacts SEO and helps your site rank higher.">

            section
              h2 5. Review Your HTML for SEO Errors
              p Use online tools like W3C Validator or SEO auditing tools to check for errors and ensure your HTML is crawlable and optimized.

            section
              h2 Conclusion
              p HTML is a powerful tool for SEO when used correctly. Focus on clean structures, semantic tags, descriptive links, and optimized meta tags to make your website more search engine-friendly.
